Critical Final Step: Clear the Cache!
Because your h1-fit-all-models-once chunk uses cache=TRUE, RStudio has memorized these failed model outputs. If you just change the code and hit Knit, it will likely load the broken models from the cache and fail again.

Before running the updated script, delete the scf_segmented_assimilation_v7_cache folder in your file directory, or use the "Clear Knitr Cache" button in RStudio. This forces the script to run the newly updated formulas from scratch.
